# To print the size of a file in bytes using zsh on macOS, you can use the
# stat builtin command, which is available in the zsh/stat module. Load
# the module and use the +size format specifier to get the size of the
# file in bytes.
zmodload zsh/stat
stat -L +size -- /path/to/your/file
# The -L flag ensures the size is reported after resolving any symbolic
# links, and +size specifies the size attribute. This method is
# efficient and directly retrieves the st_size attribute from the file's
# inode.
